	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Pac-Attack's music sounds better on the Genesis than on the Super NES. (I've rented both.) In fact, the GBA version of Pac-Attack used samples recorded from a Genesis. Magazine reviews said the same thing about the title screen music in the different Beavis and Butt-head games on the two platforms: the Super NES game's music sounded thin.
<br />
<br />But then, Disney's Pinocchio sounds far better on the Super NES, and so does Zoop.
<br />
<br />Back to the NES: European-developed games using arpeggio push the 2A03, and Sunsoft bass pushes it further.

		

		</td>
