		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />(disclaimer: I am a sega hating ninty fanboy, ignoring the dreamcast, for it was awesome)
<br />
<br />Square and Enix's SNES games are pretty much the pinnacle of pointing out why the genesis (and it's pathetic SMS-class audio) sucked. A slightly more equitable take would be that the SNES was good at orchestral stuff, the genesis at more techno stuff. When one or the other tried to cross over, the results almost invariably sucked.
<br />
<br />Good FM and wavetable music sound pretty awesome. Bad FM music is an order of magnitude worse than bad wavetable.

		

